{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"Plan-review PASSED (round 2, 0 blocking) + signed certified plan-review attestation. Advisory triage (14 findings, all non-blocking; tradeoffs accepted): (1) ReadOnlyAccess is broader than a hand-rolled describe/list policy — ACCEPTED: it's a plan-only role (no write/apply), and enumerating every describe/list action across EC2/SNS/CloudWatch/SSM/IAM/DLM/S3/EBS would be a brittle, drift-prone inline policy; ReadOnlyAccess + kms:Decrypt-via-SSM is the pragmatic least-privilege for a read-only plan. (2) repo:navapbc/rebar:* sub matches any branch/PR — ACCEPTED for a read-only role (worst case: a plan runs); can narrow to a specific ref later if desired. (3) -lock=false bypasses S3 state locking — INTENTIONAL: a read-only plan needs no lock and this avoids granting S3 PutObject. (4) SUBSTANTIVE sequencing note: the terraform-drift.yml workflow lands before rebar-terraform-plan exists in AWS, so the FIRST CI run fails until the post-merge apply creates the role — mitigation: apply AC2a promptly after merge (documented in the ticket's post-merge operator step); the check going green is itself the confirmation the role is live. (5) Title predates AC3 — cosmetic. (6) runbook/retire-path doc updates — minor follow-ups, out of scope for this change."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783784741307517001,"uuid":"7af86fb8-5339-485a-ab64-e6c16cc8778c"}